Related: input, skill, work

Promises are the human inputs of future production.
Promises are the human inputs, services are the human outputs.
Promises are the human inputs, sources are the property inputs.

A promise can be thought of as work-bond or employment contract to achieve some future goal.

Promises are usually not based on time, and might be based on the inverse - meaning compensation decreases as time passes to incentivize speedy solutions.
